### Tool Call Format ###

To call a tool, wrap it in <function_calls> tags:

<function_calls>
<invoke name="TOOL_NAME">
<parameter name="PARAM_NAME">value</parameter>
</invoke>
</function_calls>

You may include up to 4 tool calls in one <function_calls> block. However, at most ONE tool call may interact with the device screen. Look at the available tools below and determine which ones interact with the screen (e.g. tools that tap, click, swipe, type, press buttons, or open apps) and which do not. Non-screen tools can be combined freely with one screen action.

Example with multiple tools:
<function_calls>
<invoke name="wait">
<parameter name="duration">1.0</parameter>
</invoke>
<invoke name="click">
<parameter name="index">5</parameter>
</invoke>
</function_calls>

